content:
Set Up Social Customer Service with a Guided Setup Flow

Add your Twitter and Facebook accounts to turn your tweets and posts into cases in Service Cloud. Connect your social accounts, turn on Social Studio, and give your team access to your social cases.

Social Customer Service is available in all editions with the Service Cloud. Effective May 3, 2022, the Social Customer Service Starter Pack is no longer available. Customers who didn't enable it can use Social Customer Service if they have a Social Studio account.

The Twitter and Facebook setup flows are fast and easy ways to get started with Social Customer Service. When complete, tweets and posts become cases in Salesforce, and your support team can work on them.

Where to Access the Setup Flow

In Service Setup, select Service Setup. You'll see recommended setup flows based on what you've set up already. Click View All to see more.

Select the tile to launch the Twitter or Facebook flow.

Twitter and Facebook Flows

The Twitter flow enables Social Studio, authenticates your account, authorizes Salesforce, selects users for Twitter cases, and creates a permission set for access.

The Facebook flow enables Social Studio, authenticates your account, chooses Facebook pages to manage, selects users for Facebook cases, and creates a permission set for access.
title: Setting Up Social Customer Service with Guided Setup Flow
